  "text": "where the X i are known p-dimensional vectors with p < n, β is an unknown p-dimensional parameter vector, f is an unknown smooth function, and the ε i are i.i.d. random er-rors with mean zero and variance σ 2 . To estimate σ 2 , [CITATION_1] proposed a difference-based method. They applied [CITATION_2] 's optimal sequence to remove the nonparametric part, and then used a linear regression to estimate β. They used the residuals to estimate σ 2 .",
